x4freetext: Enriched 233U samples, six samples were used
Areal density ranging from 4.04E+7 to 8.46E+7 at/barn
Measurement was performed with a fission
ionization chamber, specifically built for fission
cross section measurements on radioactive U isotopes
Very low repetition rate of 0.4 Hz, long
flight path of 185 m and very high neutron flux
10E+5 n/cm2/pulse at 200 m allow for very precise
measurement over a large energy range.
GeV/c protons from the CERN proton synchrotron
incident on a natural Pb target.
Cross section determined for each energy bin
Correction for different counting efficiencies of
233U and 235 U samples, originating from different
sample thicknesses was made by simulation  using
Monte Carlo package FLUKA. Calculated correction
Correction for dead time, significant above
Added data partly presented in figs 7,8,9
of the PR/C reference, obtained by author (M.C.)
Data taken from tab. 3 of the main reference
